Java constructs annotated with our AspectJ annotations).\n    69\t * As it is built during aop.xml definitions registration we perform the type munging for perclause, ie. aspectOf() artifact\n    70\t * directly, instead of waiting for it to go thru the weaver (that we are in the middle of configuring).\n    71\t *\n    72\t * @author Alexandre Vasseur\n    73\t * @author Andy Clement\n    74\t */\n    75\tpublic class ConcreteAspectCodeGen {\n    76\t\n    77\t\tprivate final static String[] EMPTY_STRINGS = new String[0];\n    78\t\tprivate final static Type[] EMPTY_TYPES = new Type[0];\n    79\t\n    80\t\t/**\n    81\t\t * Concrete aspect definition we build for\n    82\t\t */\n    83\t\tprivate final Definition.ConcreteAspect concreteAspect;\n    84\t\n    85\t\t/**\n    86\t\t * World for which we build for\n    87\t\t */\n    88\t\tprivate final World world;\n    89\t\n    90\t\t/**\n    91\t\t * Set to true when all is checks are verified\n    92\t\t */\n    93\t\tprivate boolean isValid = false;\n    94\t\n    95\t\t/**\n    96\t\t * The parent aspect, not concretized\n    97\t\t */\n    98\t\tprivate ResolvedType parent;\n    99\t\n   100\t\t/**\n   101\t\t * Aspect perClause, used for direct munging of aspectOf artifacts\n   102\t\t */\n   103\t\tprivate PerClause perclause;\n   104\t\n   105\t\t/**\n   106\t\t * Bytecode for the generated class\n   107\t\t */\n   108\t\tprivate byte[] bytes;\n   109\t\n   110\t\t/**\n   111\t\t * Create a new generator for a concrete aspect\n   112\t\t *\n   113\t\t * @param concreteAspect the aspect definition\n   114\t\t * @param world the related world (for type resolution, etc)\n   115\t\t */\n   116\t\tConcreteAspectCodeGen(Definition.ConcreteAspect concreteAspect, World world) {\n   117\t\t\tthis.concreteAspect = concreteAspect;\n   118\t\t\tthis.world = world;\n   119\t\t}\n   120\t\n   121\t\t/**\n   122\t\t * Checks that concrete aspect is valid.\n   123\t\t *\n   124\t\t * @return true if ok, false otherwise\n  