[recv] {"type": "message_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Evaluating test configuration**\n\nI'm thinking about adding test arguments and possibly build arguments too. Right now, the existing test seems to focus only on the binary. Should I also create a test for the Java 8 branch? The report counts may not work on Java 11 and above without some workaround. \n\nIf I add a test that uses URLClassLoader and adjusts the java.version property before loading AspectJ, but the test itself shouldn’t require reflection. I can create a custom class loader for AspectJ classes, but there are challenges with loading classes and setting properties.\n\n**Analyzing class loading and test setup**\n\nI'm trying to figure out if the dynamic access report for the active class comes from the library jar in the test runtime rather than another version. Maybe using a child-first class loader could help if the class name is the same. \n\nHowever, direct reflection shouldn't be used in tests unless necessary. I could try using a system property in the @BeforeAll method, but the current test imports ClassLoaderWeavingAdaptor, which complicates class loading. I need to ensure that setting java.version won’t affect other tests or the reads of LangUtil, and I must consider restoring values after use.\n\n**Considering native image and JDK versions**\n\nI'm pondering the issue with native images and the absence of sun.misc.Unsafe.defineClass in JDK 21. It looks like calling getDeclaredMethod fails, which impacts the Method#invoke at line 1116. On the JDK 8 branch within JDK 21, Unsafe.class.getDeclaredMethod(\"defineClass\", ...) leads to a NoSuchMethodException after getUnsafe, meaning only line 1038 is actually covered, not 1116. It seems impossible to address line 1116 in JDK 21. I should also focus on covering lines 1069/1074 and 1099/1100 and think about adding JVM arguments.", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_0417ab6ecc6edbf40169f1742c