that uses URLClassLoader and adjusts the java.version property before loading AspectJ, but the test itself shouldn’t require reflection. I can create a custom class loader for AspectJ classes, but there are challenges with loading classes and setting properties.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Analyzing class loading and test setup**\\n\\nI'm trying to figure out if the dynamic access report for the active class comes from the library jar in the test runtime rather than another version. Maybe using a child-first class loader could help if the class name is the same. \\n\\nHowever, direct reflection shouldn't be used in tests unless necessary. I could try using a system property in the @BeforeAll method, but the current test imports ClassLoaderWeavingAdaptor, which complicates class loading. I need to ensure that setting java.version won’t affect other tests or the reads of LangUtil, and I must consider restoring values after use.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering native image and JDK versions**\\n\\nI'm pondering the issue with native images and the absence of sun.misc.Unsafe.defineClass in JDK 21. It looks like calling getDeclaredMethod fails, which impacts the Method#invoke at line 1116. On the JDK 8 branch within JDK 21, Unsafe.class.getDeclaredMethod(\\\"defineClass\\\", ...) leads to a NoSuchMethodException after getUnsafe, meaning only line 1038 is actually covered, not 1116. It seems impossible to address line 1116 in JDK 21. I should also focus on covering lines 1069/1074 and 1099/1100 and think about adding JVM arguments.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_lIWUYs9xoIECQ9rwasnzwtS2|fc_0417ab6ecc6edbf40169f1743a25308192a2ff4648efe285d5", "name": "edit", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/org.aspectj/aspectjweaver/1.9.7/build.gradle", "edits": [{"oldText": "dependencies {\n    testImplementation \"org.aspectj:aspectjweaver:$libraryVersion\"\n    testImplementation 'org.assertj:assertj-core:3.22.0'\n}\n\ngraalvmNative {\n", "